  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What are the competitive exams that you can give during 4 years of engineering?",
  "response": "During the 4 years of engineering, there are several competitive exams that students can consider taking to enhance their career prospects or pursue higher education. Here are some of the key exams:\n\n1. **GATE (Graduate Aptitude Test in Engineering)**: For admission to postgraduate programs and for recruitment in various public sector companies.\n\n2. **GRE (Graduate Record Examination)**: For students who wish to pursue higher studies abroad, particularly in the United States.\n\n3. **CAT (Common Admission Test)**: For admission to MBA programs in Indian Institutes of Management (IIMs) and other prestigious business schools in India.\n\n4. **TOEFL (Test of English as a Foreign Language) / IELTS (International English Language Testing System)**: For students aiming to study or work in English-speaking countries.\n\n5. **UPSC (Union Public Service Commission) Exams**: Including the Civil Services Examination for entry into various governmental positions.\n\n6. **IES (Indian Engineering Services)**: For recruitment to the technical services of the Government of India.\n\n7. **BHEL, NTPC, ONGC Recruitment Exams**: Exams conducted by various Public Sector Undertakings (PSUs) for technical and managerial positions.\n\n8. **Defense Services Exams**: \n   - **CDS (Combined Defense Services)**\n   - **AFCAT (Air Force Common Admission Test)**\n\n9. **Bank Exams**: \n   - **IBPS (Institute of Banking Personnel Selection)**\n   - **SBI PO (State Bank of India Probationary Officer)**\n   - **RBI Grade B**\n\n10. **SSC (Staff Selection Commission) Exams**: For various government jobs.\n\n11. **State-level Government Exams**: For various posts in state government departments.\n\n12. **IPMAT (Integrated Program in Management Aptitude Test)**: For admission to integrated management programs.\n\n13. **NDA (National Defense Academy) Exam**: For students interested in a career in defense right after school leading ultimately to an engineering degree.\n\n14. **MAT (Management Aptitude Test)**: For admission to MBA programs.\n\n15. **NIFT (National Institute of Fashion Technology) Entrance Exam**: For students interested in fashion technology and management.\n\n16. **Job-specific exams**: \n   - **ISRO (Indian Space Research Organization)** \n   - **DRDO (Defence Research and Development Organization)**\n\n17. **Certifications**: \n   - **Technical Certifications**: These can include exams for certifications like AWS, Cisco (CCNA, CCNP), Microsoft (Azure, Certified Solutions Expert), etc.\n   - **Project Management**: Such as PMP (Project Management Professional) for students interested in project management roles.\n\nBy planning strategically and starting early preparation, engineering students can appear for these exams as appropriate to their career goals and interests during their 4 years of study.",
